definition.value: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 18 carbons and 1 double bond (position unspecified).
A member of the class of guanidines that is decane having guanidino groups at the 1- and 10-positions.

A member of the class of ureas that is 1H-imidazole-1-carboxamide substituted by a propyl and a 2-(2,4,6-trichlorophenoxy)ethyl group at the amino nitrogen atom. A fungicide active against a wide range of diseases affecting field crops, fruit, turf and vegetables.
A pyrazole obtained by cyclocodensation of the two carbonyl groups of curcumin with hydrazine.
A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of  cholesterol with (9Z,12Z,15Z)-octadeca-9,12,15-trienoic acid.
A phenolate anion obtained by deprotonation of the 5-OH group of nogalaviketone. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A member of the class of benzothiazoles bearing hydroxy and 2-amino-2-carboxyethyl substituents at positions 4 and 6 respectively.
A member of the class of benzothiazines that is 3,4-dihydro-2H-1,4-benzothiazin-3-one bearing additional hydroxy and 2-amino-2-carboxyethyl substituents at positions 5 and 7 respectively.
A phenolate anion resulting from the removal of a proton from the phenolic hydroxy group at position 5 of methyl nogalonate. The major species at pH 7.3.
A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of  cholesterol with all-cis-icosa-8,11,14-trienoic acid.
An organosulfate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of 2-palmitoyl-3-stearoyl-2'-sulfo-alpha,alpha-trehalose arising from deprotonation of the sulfate OH group; major species at pH 7.3.
An organosulfate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of 2-palmitoyl-3,6,6'-tristearoyl-2'-sulfo-alpha,alpha-trehalose arising from deprotonation of the sulfate OH group; major species at pH 7.3.
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 20 carbons and 1 double bond (position unspecified).
A member of the class of phenothiazines that is 10H-phenothiazine having a chloro substituent at the 2-position and a 3-(4-methylpiperazin-1-yl)propyl group at the N-10 position.
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 22 carbons and 1 double bond (position unspecified).
A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of  cholesterol with  behenic acid.
An organosulfate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of 2',3'-dipalmitoyl-2-sulfo-alpha,alpha-trehalose arising from deprotonation of the sulfate OH group; major species at pH 7.3.
A 3,4-dihydro-4-hydroxyphenylpyruvate having R-configuration.
3-(4-hydroxycyclohex-2-en-1-ylidene)pyruvate obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of 3-[(1E,4R)-4-hydroxycyclohex-2-en-1-ylidene]pyruvic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of (3E)-3-[(1R,5R,6S)-5-hydroxy-7-oxabicyclo[4.1.0]heptan-2-ylidene]pyruvic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.

A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-[(1R,2S,5R,6S)-5-hydroxy-7-oxabicyclo[4.1.0]heptan-2-yl]pyruvic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of L-dihydroanticapsin; major species at pH 7.3.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 3-hydroxy-2,4-pentanedione 5-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of cyclohexenones that is (1R,5S,6R)-4-amino-5-hydroxy-1-(hydroxymethyl)-7-oxabicyclo[4.1.0]hept-3-en-2-one in which one of the amino hydrogens is replaced by an acetyl group.
A member of the class of cyclitols that is valiolone in which the stererocentre at position 5 has been inverted.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 2-epi-5-epi-valiolone 7-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the secondary amino group of acarbose; major species at pH 7.3.
Any organic heteropolycyclic compound that is derived from a cladoniamide.

An organic heterohexacyclic compound that is cladoniamide B in which the chlorine attached to the methoxy-bearing indole moiety is replaced by a hydrogen. It has been isolated from the culture broth of Streptomyces uncialis.

8a,13-dihydrobenzo[2,3]pyrrolo[3',4':5,6]indolizino[8,7-b]indole-6,8(5aH,7H)-dione which is substituted by chlorines at positions 2 and 10, hydroxy groups at positions 5a and 8a, a methoxy group at position 14, and a methyl group at position 7 (the 5aR,8aS diastereoisomer). It has been isolated from the culture broth of Streptomyces uncialis.
An organic heterohexacyclic compound that is cladoniamide B in which both of the chlorines are replaced by hydrogen. It has been isolated from the culture broth of Streptomyces uncialis.

An organic heteropentacyclic compound that is cladoniamide E in which the chlorine attached to the methoxy-bearing indole moiety is replaced by a hydrogen. It has been isolated from the culture broth of Streptomyces uncialis.

An organic heteropentacyclic compound that is 7,12-dihydro-6H-pyrido[1,2-a:3,4-b']diindole substituted by chloro groups at positions 2 and 9, a hydroxy group and an N-methyl carbamyl group at position 6, a methoxy group at position 13, and an oxo group at position 7 (the 6R stereoisomer). It is isolated from the culture broth of Streptomyces uncialis.

An organic heteropentacyclic compound that is cladoniamide G in which the chlorine attached to the methoxy-bearing indole moiety is replaced by a hydrogen. It has been isolated from the culture broth of Streptomyces uncialis.
A N-acylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as tricosanoyl.
An amino trisaccharide comprising of three 2-amino-2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose units joined by beta-(1->4) linkages.
An alpha-amino-acid cation that is the conjugate acid of 3-amino-L-alanine.
A N-acylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as (17Z)-hexacosenoyl.
A straight-chain saturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of pentacosanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A monounsaturated fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 25 carbons and 1 double bond (position unspecified).
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxypentacosanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 25 carbons and 1 double bond (position unspecified).

A chondramide that is chondramide C in which the pro-S hydrogen at position 2 of the beta-tyrosine residue is replaced by a methoxy group. It is produced by strains of the myxobacterium, Chondromyces crocatus.
A chondramide that is chondramide A in which the hydrogen at position 2 of the indole moiety has been replaced by a chlorine. It is produced by strains of the myxobacterium, Chondromyces crocatus.

A chondramide formally obtained from N-[(2S,4E,6R,7R)-7-hydroxy-2,4,6-trimethyloct-4-enoyl]-L-alanyl-Nalpha-methyl-D-tryptophanyl-beta-R-beta-tyrosine by intramolecular condensation of the alcoholic hydroxy group with the carboxy group of the beta-tyrosine residue. It is produced by strains of the myxobacterium, Chondromyces crocatus.
A chondramide that is chondramide C in which the hydrogen at position 2 of the indole moiety is replaced by a chlorine.  It is produced by strains of the myxobacterium, Chondromyces crocatus.
Any of the 18-membered ring cyclodepsipeptides produced by strains of the myxobacterium, Chondromyces crocatus.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol that has myristoyl and palmitoyl as 1- and 2-acyl groups respectively.
